vZBYSQtTbY9MaYu5qNuU8Q
Ok time for the obligatory annual non-food-related review.   Piestewa definitely makes its way to my top 3 for hikes in Phoenix. Setting aside the fact that I've only hiked 3 mountain trails in Phoenix so far, it's actually probably my favorite one to do.  1. Convenience - It's only about a 10 min drive from my apartment, making this the perfect location for people who also live at my apartment complex  2. Going the distance - It's a decently arduous 3 mile hike - 1.5miles up and 1.5 miles back..ish (we had a fit-bit user with us to verify this distance)  3. Workouts & instagrams - It's as intense or leisurely as you make it. Good mixture of incline, rocks, 10ft tall cacti, and a gorgeous 360 degrees of Phoenician cityscape.  Unfortunately Piestewa is no hidden jewel and there are droves of people out in full force in every not-summer month. The only time I would guess the parking lots aren't full would be from about 11am-?? I'm not really sure when the evening crowds start their treks as I've only done this hike in the morning.

