Tasty, authentic vietnamese food at vietnamese prices! This place is always pretty packed/busy, but the service is fast and the food is bountiful and filling.  While the pho is good I prefer to go with the wonton noodle soup or the com tam dac biet. I also feel a little less guilty whenever eating here because it tastes more like a homecooked meal than a greasy, heavier meal I'd order at some other sit down restaurant. Only a slightly less guilty though. Whatever, I'm still coming back here multiple times a week! They close around 830 or 9pm too so make sure to plan ahead of time so you don't arrive right as they lock the doors on ya.

